   BELL ATLANTIC Corp. (Arlington, Va.) -- Thomas C. Burns,
president and chief executive of Bell Atlantic's Chesapeake &amp;
Potomac Telephone Co. of West Virginia, was named senior
executive and chief representative for Bell Atlantic and
Ameritech Corp. in New Zealand. Both companies joined two New
Zealand concerns last month to buy the state-owned
telecommunications company. Mr. Burns will be succeeeded as
president and chief executive of Chesapeake &amp; Potomac in West
Virginia by David E. Berry, currently vice president of human
resources for Bell Atlantic. Mr. Berry, in turn, will be
succeeded by Charles W. Christ Jr., currently vice president
in charge of operations for Chesapeake &amp; Potomac Telephone
Co. of Virginia.
